{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-08-09-how-to-add-moving-text-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add moving text in react js, you can use . It will add moving text in react js. Today, I am going to show you, how to‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add moving text in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">animation: marquee 10s linear infinite;</code>. It will add moving text in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add moving text in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import react component.</h3>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Create a Component.</h3>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">className=\"marquee\" </code> to add moving text in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"marquee\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>This is some moving text<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Add moving text example.</h3>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">./App.css</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">animation: marquee 10s linear infinite;</code> to add moving text in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">MovingText</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"marquee\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>This is some moving text<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>p<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> MovingText<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.css</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.marquee</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">overflow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> hidden<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">background-color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #f1f1f1<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  \n  <span class=\"token selector\">.marquee p</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> inline-block<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">white-space</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> nowrap<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">animation</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> marquee 10s linear infinite<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  \n  <span class=\"token atrule\"><span class=\"token rule\">@keyframes</span> marquee</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token selector\">from</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">transform</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">translateX</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>100%<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token selector\">to</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token property\">transform</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">translateX</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>-100%<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">animation: marquee 10s linear infinite;</code> to add moving text in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/ec897/add-moving-text.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.645569620253163%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRkAAAABXRUJQVlA4IDQAAACwAgCdASoUAAYALplotFoiqCgoCACYSzgABc6LawAA/vY0eSh1GFrUhQaABZgGz3i4AAAA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add,  moving, text\"\n        title=\"React, add,  moving, text\"\n        src=\"/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/8aab1/add-moving-text.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/81b7c/add-moving-text.webp 158w,\n/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/6ea66/add-moving-text.webp 315w,\n/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/8aab1/add-moving-text.webp 630w,\n/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/a70f5/add-moving-text.webp 945w,\n/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/4ef06/add-moving-text.webp 1260w,\n/static/20d902f2a46397337f052368ad0690aa/ec897/add-moving-text.webp 1366w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to add moving text in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"August 09, 2024","description":"Example of add moving text in react js with step by step tutorial - aHoisting","social_image":{"absolutePath":"/Users/mac/Documents/hoisting/ahoisting/static/media/template/reactjs.jpg"}}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add minimize button in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-08-09-how-to-add-minimize-button-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add mime type in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-08-08-how-to-add-mime-type-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2024-08-09-how-to-add-moving-text-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2024-08-09-how-to-add-minimize-button-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2024-08-08-how-to-add-mime-type-in-react-js/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2555585279","2714594843","